<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2718] CLONE -JAVA_HOME with Backslash at end results in Error JAVA_HOME not set</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2718</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On my system I have JAVA_HOME set to &quot;C:\JDK\&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
This results in an error message when starting GROOVY:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;JAVA_HOME not set&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I change JAVA_HOME to &quot;C:\JDK&quot; everything works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be a litte disturbing for new users and should be easy to fix, I guess.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Greetings,&lt;br/&gt;
   Malte&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows XP Groovy 1.0-beta-6</environment>
